info.senderName: NWS Key West (Key West - The Florida Keys)
info.headline: Coastal Flood Warning issued September 29 at 3:57AM EDT until September 30 at 6:00AM EDT by NWS Key West
info.description: ...COASTAL FLOOD WARNING NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 AM EDT FRIDAY... * WHAT...Coastal flooding will continue in Bayside communities of Key Largo today and tonight. With persistent west to northwest winds, these areas will see very high water levels of 2 to 3 feet above normal tides continue, with little if any relief at low tide. * WHERE...Upper Florida Keys, mainly the Bayside communities of Key Largo. * WHEN...Until 6 AM EDT Friday. * IMPACTS...Numerous roads may be closed. Low lying property including homes, businesses, and some critical infrastructure will be inundated. Some shoreline erosion will occur.
info.instruction: Take the necessary actions to protect flood-prone property. If travel is required, do not drive around barricades or through water of unknown depth.
